	<h2>Sustainably Sourced Wood: FSC-Certified Lumber</h2>

	<h3>Understanding FSC Certification</h3>
	<p>Forest Stewardship Council (FSC) certification ensures wood products come from responsibly managed forests that provide environmental, social, and economic benefits. FSC-certified lumber represents a sustainable choice when you want the natural beauty of wood with environmental accountability.</p>

	<p>FSC forests must meet rigorous standards including:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Maintaining biodiversity and protecting endangered species habitats</li>
		<li>Protecting indigenous peoples' rights and forest workers</li>
		<li>Implementing sustainable harvest rates that don't exceed forest growth</li>
		<li>Protecting water quality and soil stability</li>
		<li>Prohibiting conversion of natural forests to plantations</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Best FSC-Certified Wood Options for Stockton</h3>
	<p><strong>FSC-Certified Redwood:</strong> Naturally resistant to rot and insects, redwood performs exceptionally well in Stockton's climate. California-sourced FSC redwood minimizes transportation impact while supporting local sustainable forestry. Cost: $25-45 per linear foot installed.</p>

	<p><strong>FSC-Certified Cedar:</strong> Aromatic, beautiful, and naturally durable, cedar resists warping and splitting in hot weather. Requires less maintenance than pine but needs regular sealing in Stockton sun. Cost: $20-40 per linear foot installed.</p>

	<p><strong>FSC-Certified Pressure-Treated Pine:</strong> Most affordable certified wood option. Modern treatments are safer and more environmentally friendly than old arsenic-based preservatives. Cost: $15-30 per linear foot installed.</p>

	<h3>Where to Source FSC-Certified Lumber in Stockton Area</h3>
